Video footage of what appears to be a woman beating two girls has sparked outrage on social media, with many calling on officials to take action. DispatchLIVE reported that the woman beating the young girls is a church leader at the Endumisweni Faith Mission in Mdantsane, near East London. The two girls in the video footage, which has since gone viral, spoke to DispatchLIVE about the incident. They said they were being punished for a short video they had posted on WhatsApp in which they were seen dancing at a shopping centre. DispatchLIVE reported that at least 15 otherÂ  members of the church have come forward since the video emerged, detailing their experiences at the church. As the video made its rounds on Twitter, people accused the church of being a cult and called for action.